ork%20City%20and%20how%20little%20you%20get%20for%20the%20hefty%20price.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20I%20left%20LA%2C%20I%20was%20paying%20%241%2C100%20a%20month%20for%20a%20massive%20studio%20in%20West%20Hollywood%20in%20a%20complex%20with%20a%20swimming%20pool%2C%20gym%2C%20and%20parking.%20My%20first%20apartment%20in%20New%20York%20was%20%24200%20more%20for%20significantly%20less%20space%20and%20amenities.%20I%20paid%20rent%20from%20scholarship%20funds%2C%20grants%2C%20and%20student%20loans.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20living%20in%20studios%20in%20New%20York%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20sustainable%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20paid%20%241%2C300%20for%20a%20tiny%20studio%20on%2064th%20and%20West%20End%20in%202009.%20It%20was%20so%20small%20I%20slept%20on%20a%20pullout%20couch%20that%20couldn't%20even%20open%20fully%2C%20and%20I%20slept%20at%20a%20slant.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20graduated%20from%20college%20in%202010%20and%20worked%20as%20a%20coordinator%20at%20a%20PR%20agency.%20I%20lived%20in%20the%20Lower%20East%20Side%20and%20paid%20%241%2C450%20for%20a%20slightly%20larger%20studio%20on%20Stanton%20and%20Ludlow.%20I%20had%20mostly%20lived%20alone%20since%20I%20was%2017%20and%20preferred%20not%20to%20have%20roommates.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20loved%20that%20apartment%2C%20but%20someone%20started%20stalking%20me%20shortly%20after%20I%20moved%20on.%20It%20went%20on%20for%20months%20as%20the%20NYPD%20investigated.%20Fearing%20for%20my%20safety%2C%20an%20acquaintance%20convinced%20me%20to%20move%20into%20a%20two-bedroom%20apartment%20on%201st%20St%20and%201st%20Ave%20with%20security%20guards%20in%20March%202013.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3ERoommates%20are%20a%20necessary%20evil%20as%20a%20young%20person%20living%20in%20New%20York%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInitially%2C%20I%20split%20the%20rent%20with%20my%20roommate%20based%20on%20room%20size.%20I%20took%20the%20smaller%20room%20for%20%241%2C450.%20My%20roommate%20abruptly%20decided%20to%20leave%20New%20York%20four%20months%20into%20our%20two-year%20lease.%20She%20made%20it%20challenging%20to%20find%20a%20replacement.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUltimately%2C%20a%20new%20roommate%20was%20able%20to%20take%20over%20her%20portion%20of%20the%20lease.%20I%20was%20so%20exhausted%20that%20I%20let%20the%20new%20roommate%20live%20in%20the%20larger%20room%20with%20a%20built-in%20closet%2C%20but%20we%20still%20split%20the%20%243%2C280%20rent%2C%20each%20paying%20%241%2C640%20before%20utilities.%20I%20lived%20with%20this%20arrangement%20from%20October%202013%20until%20March%202015.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20I%20was%20a%20Senior%20Manager%20at%20a%20strategic%20fashion%20branding%20agency%20in%20New%20York%20on%20%245%2C582%20a%20month%20after%20taxes%20and%20401(k)%20contributions.%20Around%2030%25%20of%20my%20income%20was%20going%20toward%20my%20rent.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EMonthly%20expenses%20like%20gyms%20and%20entertainment%20rack%20up%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20often%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20living%20from%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck.%20There%20was%20immense%20pressure%20to%20have%20a%20wardrobe%20of%20trendy%20pieces.%20I%20had%20enough%20clothing%2C%20most%20bought%20on%20sale%2C%20to%20fill%20a%20closet%20and%20two%20clothing%20racks.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20monthly%20expenses%20added%20up%20quickly%20with%20student%20loan%20payments%2C%20gym%20memberships%2C%20exercise%20classes%2C%20taxis%2C%20and%20going%20out%20several%20times%20a%20week%20for%20dinner%20and%20drinks.%20My%20savings%20were%20essentially%20nonexistent.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3ELeaving%20the%20city%20at%2025%20wasn't%20an%20easy%20decision%20for%20me%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20loved%20my%20life%20in%20Manhattan%2C%20had%20wonderful%20friends%2C%20a%20decent%20apartment%2C%20and%20was%20excelling%20at%20my%20career.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EToward%20the%20end%20of%202014%2C%20I%20was%20notified%20I%20would%20be%20promoted.%20I%20knew%20other%20people%20on%20that%20level%20were%20making%20six%20figures.%20I%20should%20have%20been%20elated%2C%20but%20I%20wasn't.%20I%20realized%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20spend%20the%20rest%20of%20my%2020s%20sitting%20at%20a%20desk%20for%2010%20hours%20daily.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202015%2C%20I%20resigned%20from%20my%20role.%20I%20planned%20to%20move%20to%20Uruguay%2C%20where%20my%20father%20was%20from%2C%20and%20start%20a%20nonprofit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20months%20leading%20up%20to%20my%20departure%2C%20I%20saved%20around%20%2410%2C000%20by%20selling%20my%20designer%20clothes%20at%20consignment%20shops.%20Letting%20go%20of%20Christian%20Louboutin%20shoes%20and%20Louis%20Vuitton%20handbags%20was%20painful%2C%20but%20with%20each%20sale%2C%20I%20could%20envision%20myself%20traveling%20to%20some%20far-off%20destination.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThere%20are%20benefits%20to%20being%20a%20twenty-something%20in%20New%20York%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20benefits%20of%20living%20in%20New%20York%20in%20my%2020s%20were%20having%20access%20to%20the%20best%20art%2C%20dining%20establishments%2C%20and%20music%20in%20the%20world.%20Also%2C%20my%20career%20thrived%20quickly.%20I%20had%20nine%20internships%20during%20my%20degree.%20By%20the%20time%20I%20graduated%2C%20I%20had%20several%20full-time%20job%20offers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELife%20in%20New%20York%20was%20never%20boring%2C%20but%20it%20was%20expensive.%20I%20got%20caught%20up%20in%20how%20superficial%20the%20fashion%20industry%20is.%20I%20was%20a%20snob%20and%20hardly%20left%20Manhattan.%20I%20experienced%20difficult%20moments%20that%20challenged%20my%20wholesome%20Midwestern%20upbringing%20and%20sunny%20California%20disposition.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20thought%20I%20had%20to%20live%20in%20New%20York%20to%20be%20successful%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20worth%20the%20lack%20of%20saving%20in%20my%2020s.%20Leaving%20the%20city%20at%2025%20was%20the%20best%20decision%20for%20my%20well-being%20and%20wallet.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EI've%20been%20able%20to%20save%206%20figures%20because%20I%20don't%20rent%20in%20New%20York%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI'm%20now%2034%20and%20have%20been%20renting%20apartments%20for%20half%20my%20life.%20I%20haven't%20moved%20back%20to%20the%20States%20since%20leaving%20New%20York.%20I've%20mostly%20lived%20alone%20in%20modern%20apartments%20in%20trendy%20neighborhoods.%20I've%20lived%20in%20Madrid%2C%20Chaing%20Mai%2C%20Thailand%3B%20Hoi%20An%2C%20Vietnam%3B%20Montevideo%2C%20Uruguay%3B%20and%20Puerto%20Vallarta%2C%20Mexico%2C%20and%20never%20paid%20more%20than%20%24800%20a%20month%20for%20housing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20freelance%20journalist%2C%20I%20could%20never%20afford%20the%20quality%20of%20apartments%20I've%20become%20accustomed%20to%20if%20I%20lived%20in%20New%20York.%20I've%20saved%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-freelance-writer-earned-over-10000-dollars-in-month-2020-10%3Fr%3DMX%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Eover%20six%20figures%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20years%20%E2%80%94%20mostly%20because%20I'm%20not%20paying%20Manhattan%20rent.%20I'm%20based%20in%20Puerto%20Vallarta%2C%20Mexico%20where%20I%20pay%20%24730%20a%20month%20for%20a%20gigantic%20one-bedroom%20with%20a%20California%20King%20bed%2C%20a%20balcony%20overlooking%20the%20mountains%2C%20a%20swimming%20pool%2C%20and%20weekly%20maid%20service.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20freelancer%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20steady%20guaranteed%20