stinations%20that%20weren't%20on%20their%20boarding%20passes%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20passengers%20travelling%20from%20Stansted%20to%20Newquay%20who%20eventually%20diverted%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fuk.news.yahoo.com%2Fstorm-isha-creates-flight-diversion-142821278.html%3F%5C%22%3EMalaga%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20that%20was%20consistently%20described%20by%20passengers%20was%20that%20parts%20of%20the%20flights%20and%20the%20attempted%20landings%20were%20some%20of%20the%20most%20unnerving%20they'd%20ever%20experienced%2C%20due%20to%20turbulence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETurbulence%20results%20from%20uneven%20air%20movement%2C%20which%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1029%2F2023GL103814%5C%22%3Eincreasing%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20frequency.%20If%20you%20turn%20your%20hair%20dryer%20on%20at%20home%20and%20hold%20it%20still%2C%20the%20air%20moves%20at%20a%20constant%20rate%2C%20but%20once%20you%20begin%20drying%20your%20hair%20and%20moving%20the%20hairdryer%20around%2C%20the%20air%20movement%20becomes%20uneven%2C%20that%20is%20to%20say%2C%20turbulent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20turbulence%20may%20be%20unnerving%20and%20make%20you%20feel%20unwell%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20recognise%20that%20it%20is%20very%20common%20and%20typically%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F18018437%2F%5C%22%3Enothing%20to%20worry%20about%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20you're%20in%20your%20seat%20with%20your%20seatbelt%20fastened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EHow%20the%20body%20detects%20and%20responds%20to%20turbulence%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20body%20recognises%20itself%20within%20any%20environment.%20Its%20relationship%20with%20objects%20in%20terms%20of%20distance%20and%20direction%20is%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FB9780123750006003414%5C%22%3Espatial%20orientation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20flying%2C%20this%20is%20typically%20moving%20forwards%2C%20ascending%2C%20some%20turns%20and%20a%20descent.%20However%2C%20turbulence%20disrupts%20this%20relationship%20and%20confuses%20the%20sensory%20information%20being%20received%20by%20the%20brain%20%E2%80%93%20it%20makes%20the%20body%20want%20to%20respond%20or%20recalibrate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20inner%20ears%20play%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20all%20this.%20It%20consists%20of%20complex%20apparatuses%20that%20undertake%20more%20than%20hearing.%20These%20include%20the%20cochlea%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fbooks%2FNBK279394%2F%5C%22%3Ethree%20semi-circular%20canals%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fradiopaedia.org%2Farticles%2Futricle-ear%3Flang%3Dgb%5C%22%3Ethe%20utricle%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fradiopaedia.org%2Farticles%2Fsaccule-ear-1%3Flang%3Dgb%5C%22%3Ethe%20saccule%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cochlea%20is%20responsible%20for%20hearing.%20It%20converts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fbooks%2FNBK531483%2F%5C%22%3Esound%20energy%20into%20electrical%20energy%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20is%20then%20%E2%80%9Cheard%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20brain.%20The%20remaining%20structures%20are%20responsible%20for%20the%20balance%20and%20position%20of%20the%20head%20and%20body.%20The%20semi-circular%20canals%20are%20positioned%20in%20a%20vertical%20(side%20to%20side)%2C%20horizontal%20and%20front-to-back%20plane%2C%20detecting%20movement%20in%20a%20nodding%2C%20shaking%20and%20touching%20ear-to-shoulder%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAttached%20to%20these%20canals%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fbooks%2FNBK532978%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20utricle%20and%20saccule%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20can%20detect%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fbooks%2FNBK10792%2F%5C%22%3Emovement%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cell.com%2Fcurrent-biology%2Fpdf%2FS0960-9822(05)00837-7.pdf%5C%22%3Eacceleration%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20these%20apparatuses%20use%20microscopic%20hair%20cells%20in%20a%20specialised%20fluid%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fbooks%2FNBK531505%2F%5C%22%3Eendolymph%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20flows%20with%20the%20head%20to%20create%20a%20sense%20of%20movement.%20When%20the%20plane%20encounters%20turbulence%2C%20this%20fluid%20moves%20around%2C%20but%20unpredictably.%20It%20takes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fbooks%2FNBK518976%2F%5C%22%3Eabout%20ten%20to%2020%20seconds%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20fluid%20to%20recalibrate%20its%20position%2C%20while%20the%20brain%20struggles%20to%20understand%20what%20is%20going%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20aircraft%20hits%20turbulence%2C%20the%20balance%20apparatus%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frontiersin.org%2Farticles%2F10.3389%2Ffneur.2023.949227%2Ffull%5C%22%3Ecannot%20distinguish%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20movement%20of%20the%20plane%20from%20that%20of%20the%20head%2C%20so%20the%20brain%20interprets%20the%20aircraft%20movement%20as%20that%20of%20the%20head%20or%20body.%20But%20this%20doesn't%20match%20the%20visual%20information%20being%20received%2C%20which%20causes%20sensory%20confusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20the%20inner%20ear%20causes%20so%20much%20confusion%20is%20because%20during%20flights%20you%20are%20devoid%20of%20your%20primary%20sensory%20tool%20relative%20to%20the%20external%20environment%20%E2%80%93%20your%20sight%20and%20the%20horizon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEighty%20per%20cent%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fbooks%2FNBK518976%2F%5C%22%3Espatial%20information%3C%2Fa%3E%20comes%20from%20your%20eyes%20during%20flight.%20However%2C%20you%20only%20have%20the%20seat%20in%20front%20of%20you%20or%20the%20cabin%20as%20a%20reference%20point%2C%20which%20means%20your%20inner%20ear%20becomes%20the%20dominant%20sensory%20message%20to%20the%20brain%20during%20turbulence%20and%20disrupts%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fbooks%2FNBK545297%2F%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cvestibulo-ocular%20reflex%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20reflex%20keeps%20your%20vision%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4130651%2F%5C%22%3Ealigned%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20your%20balance%20or%20expected%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVision%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC6777262%2F%5C%22%3Emost%20valued%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20senses%20and%20one-third%20of%20the%20brain%20is%20attributed%20to%20its%20function%2C%20reinforcing%20its%20importance%20in%20spatial%20orientation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20sensory%20mixed%20messaging%20often%20results%20in%20things%20like%20dizziness%20and%20sweating%20as%20well%20as%20gastrointestinal%20symptoms%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airmedicaljournal.com%2Farticle%2FS1067-991X(02)70038-2%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Enausea%20and%20vomiting%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMotion%20sickness%20can%20be%20triggered%20by%20turbulence%20and%20although%20research%20into%20specific%20airsickness%20is%20limited%2C%20other%20modes%20that%20induce%20motion%20sickness%20suggest%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F16018346%2F%5C%22%3Ewomen%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F26466829%2F%5C%22%3Emore%20susceptible%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20men%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F16235881%2F%5C%22%3Eearly%20stages%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20menstrual%20cycle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20turbulence%20also%20causes%20an%20increase%20in%20your%20heart%20rate%2C%20which%20is%20already%20higher%20than%20normal%20when%20flying%20because%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F15819766%2F%5C%22%3Edecrease%20in%20oxygen%20saturation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWhat%20about%20the%20pilots%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommercial%20pilots%20accrue%20thousands%20of%20hours%20at%20the%20controls%2C%20they%20are%20subject%20to%20the%20same%20forces%20as%20the%20passengers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20they%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fmilmed%2Farticle%2F180%2F11%2F1135%2F4160573%5C%22%3Eadapt%20to%20these%20forces%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F15828634%2F%5C%22%3Eexperiences%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20they%20also%20have%20a%20couple%20of%20additional%20resources%20that%20most%20passengers%20don't.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20have%20the%20view%20out%20of%20the%20cockpit%20windows%2C%20so%20have%20a%20horizon%20to%20use%20as%20a%20reference%20point%20and%20can%20see%20what%20lies%20immediately%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20it%20is%20cloudy%20or%20visibility%20is%20low%2C%20their%20instruments%20provide%20additional%20visual%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.faa.gov%2Fsites%2Ffaa.gov%2Ffiles%2Fregulations_policies%2Fhandbooks_manuals%2Faviation%2Fphak%2F19_phak_ch17.pdf%5C%22%3Ereference%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20position%20of%20the%20aircraft.%20This%20doesn't%20mean%20they%20are%20immune%20to%20the%20effects%20of%20turbulence%2C%20with%20some%20studies%20reporting%20up%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F26540704%2F%5C%22%3E71%25%20of%20trainee%20pilots%3C%2Fa%3E%20reporting%20episodes%20of%20airsickness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EHow%20to%20reduce%20the%20discomfort%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20window%20seat%20can%20help%2C%20or%20even%20looking%20out%20the%20window.%20This%20gives%20the%20brain%20some%20sensory%20information%20through%20visual%20pathways%2C%20helping%20calm%20the%20brain%20in%20response%20to%20the%20vestibular%20information%20it%20is%20receiving.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20can%20get%20one%2C%20a%20seat%20towards%20the%20front%20or%20over%20the%20wing%20reduces%20the%20effects%20of%20turbulence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeep%20or%20rhythmical%20breathing%20can%20help%20reduce%20motion%20sickness%20induced%20by%20turbulence.%20Focusing%20on%20your%20breathing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F25945662%2F%5C%22%3Ecalms%20the%20nervous%20system%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDon't%20reach%20for%20the%20alcohol.%20While%20you%20may%20feel%20it%20calms%20your%20nerves%2C%20if%20you%20hit%20turbulence%20it's%20going%20to%20interfere%20with%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F7610847%2F%5C%22%3Evisual%20and%20auditory%20processing%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20increase%20the%20likelihood%20of%20vomiting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20suffer%20from%20motion%20sickness%20and%20are%20worried%20about%20turbulence%20while%20flying%2C%20then%20there%20are%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC6241144%2F%5C%22%3Edrugs%20that%20can%20help%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20certain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nhs.uk%2Fmedicines%2Fcinnarizine%2Fabout-cinnarizine%2F%5C%22%3Eantihistamines%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20remember%20that%20although%20turbulence%20can%20be%20unpleasant%2C%20aircraft%20are%20designed%20to%20withstand%20the%20forces%20it%20generates%20and%20many%20passengers%2C%20even%20frequent%20fliers%2C%20will%20rarely%20encounter%20the%20most%20severe%20categories%20of%20turbulence%20because%20pilots%20actively%20plan%20routes%20to%20avoid%20it.%3Cimg%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F221780%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E(%3Cstrong%3EAuthor%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fadam-taylor-283950%5C%22%3EAdam%20Taylor%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Professor%20and%20Director%20of%20the%20Clinical