tty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20new%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20report%20contained%20new%20insights%20into%20nonreligious%20Americans.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20so-called%C2%A0%26quot%3Bnones%26quot%3B%20have%20been%20rising%20for%20decades%20and%20now%20make%20up%20nearly%2030%25%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPew%20found%20many%20nones%20still%20believe%20in%20God%20or%20another%20higher%20power%20and%20identify%20as%20spiritual.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rise%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bnones%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20Americans%20who%20report%20having%20no%20religious%20affiliation%20%E2%80%94%20has%20been%20happening%20for%20decades%2C%20sparking%20questions%20and%20concerns%20about%20what%20the%20decline%20in%20religiosity%20could%20mean%20for%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20detailed%20report%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Freligion%2F2024%2F01%2F24%2Freligious-nones-in-america-who-they-are-and-what-they-believe%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20Wednesday%20sheds%20some%20new%20light%20on%20who%20these%20people%20actually%20are%20%E2%80%94%20and%20undermines%20some%20perceptions%20about%20all%20of%20them%20being%20anti-religion%20or%20anti-God.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20Pew%20found%2028%25%20of%20Americans%20fell%20into%20the%20nones%20category%2C%20which%20includes%20people%20who%2C%20when%20asked%20about%20their%20religion%2C%20say%20they%20are%20atheists%2C%20agnostics%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bnothing%20in%20particular.%26quot%3B%20That's%20up%20from%2016%25%20in%202007%20and%205%25%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Freligion%2F2022%2F09%2F13%2Fmodeling-the-future-of-religion-in-america%2Fpf_2022-09-13_religious-projections_01-01%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1972%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20of%20nones%2C%2063%25%2C%20are%20%26quot%3Bnothing%20in%20particular%2C%26quot%3B%20while%2020%25%20identified%20as%20agnostic%20and%2017%25%20were%20atheist.%20Nones%20tend%20to%20be%20younger%20than%20the%20religiously%20affiliated%2C%20and%20they%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20identify%20as%20liberal.%20They%20include%20nearly%20equal%20numbers%20of%20men%20and%20women%2C%20and%20the%20racial%20breakdown%20is%20similar%20to%20that%20of%20religious%20Americans.%20However%2C%20atheists%20and%20agnostics%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20white%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20they%20do%20not%20identify%20with%20a%20religion%2C%20most%20nones%20say%20they%20believe%20in%20God%20or%20another%20higher%20power%20%E2%80%94%20just%20not%20the%20God%20that%20is%20described%20in%20the%20Bible%2C%20according%20to%20Pew.%20Half%20say%20spirituality%20is%20important%20to%20them%20or%20that%20they%20identify%20as%20spiritual.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20specific%20reasons%20they%20are%20nonreligious%2C%2060%25%20of%20nones%20emphasized%20their%20questioning%20of%20many%20religious%20teachings%2C%20while%2047%25%20cited%20not%20liking%20religious%20organizations.%20Around%2044%25%20also%20said%20they%20lacked%20the%20need%20or%20time%20for%20religion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20not%20all%20nones%20express%20hostility%20toward%20religion.%20While%2043%25%20said%20religion%20causes%20more%20harm%20than%20good%2C%2041%25%20said%20it%20causes%20equal%20amounts%20of%20harm%20and%20good.%20While%2080%25%20agreed%20with%20the%20statement%20%26quot%3Breligion%20causes%20division%20and%20intolerance%2C%26quot%3B%2058%25%20said%20religion%20%26quot%3Bhelps%20society%20by%20giving%20people%20meaning%20and%20purpose%20in%20their%20lives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20'nones'%20have%20a%20very%20negative%20view%20of%20religion%2C%20but%20'nones'%20on%20the%20whole%20express%20mixed%20views%20rather%20than%20outright%20hostility%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20found%20that%2C%20in%20general%2C%20nones%20were%20somewhat%20less%20civically%20and%20politically%20engaged%20than%20religious%20people.%20However%2C%20the%20difference%20fell%20away%20for%20atheists%20and%20agnostics%20specifically%2C%20who%20were%20equally%20and%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20civically%20engaged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20often%20just%20the%20'nothing%20in%20particular'%20group%20that%20stands%20out%20for%20having%20relatively%20low%20levels%20of%20civic%20behavior%2C%20such%20as%20voting%20and%20volunteering%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20compared%20to%20the%20nearly%2060%25%20of%20religious%20people%20who%20don't%20regularly%20attend%20church%2C%20nones%20were%20about%20equally%20as%20likely%20to%20have%20volunteered%20in%20the%20past%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPew%20researchers%20noted%20that%20the%20number%20of%20nones%20fell%203%20percentage%20points%20last%20year%20from%2031%25%20in%202022.%20However%2C%20they%20said%20it%20was%20too%20soon%20to%20tell%20if%20that%20meant%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2024%2F01%2F24%2Fhas-the-rise-of-religious-nones-come-to-an-end-in-the-us%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erise%20in%20the%20nones%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20finally%20plateauing%20after%20decades%20of%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPew%20said%20most%20of%20the%20data%20used%20for%20the%20report%20came%20from%20a%20survey%20it%20conducted%20in%20July%20and%20August%20among%2011%2C201%20respondents%20who%20were%20part%20of%20its%20American%20Trends%20Panel%2C%20an%20online%20survey%20panel%20recruited%20nationally%20with%20random%20sampling.%20Pew%20conducted%20interviews%20with%203%2C317%20respondents%20who%20were%20classified%20as%20religious%20nones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-the-nones-more-americans-religiously-unaffiliated-who-are-they-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2