Hours%20after%20West%20Bengal%20chief%20minister%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20announced%20that%20she%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fas-bengal-congress-and-tmc-spar-rahul-gandhi-insists-seat-sharing-talks-still-on%5C%22%3Ego%20it%20alone%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20in%20West%20Bengal%2C%20the%20Congress%20on%20Wednesday%20sought%20to%20contain%20the%20damage%20to%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20and%20said%20that%20she%20is%20an%20%E2%80%9Cimportant%20pillar%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20bloc%2C%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9Cspeed%20breakers%E2%80%9D%20along%20the%20journey%20do%20not%20imply%20an%20end%20to%20the%20journey%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20TMC%20on%20the%20other%20hand%20has%20reiterated%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20position%20and%20said%20that%20in%20West%20Bengal%20it%20is%20the%20only%20party%20that%20can%20defeat%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3ETMC%20spokesperson%20Sushmita%20Dev%20said%20that%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20AITC%20(All%20India%20Trinamool%20Congress)%20was%20very%20emphatically%20clear%20about%20finishing%20seat-sharing%20talks%20by%20September%2030.%20But%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t%20happen.%20Then%20December%203%20came%20when%20the%20assembly%20election%20results%20were%20announced%20and%20then%20it%20was%20decided%20let%E2%80%99s%20conclude%20seat-sharing%20talks%20by%20December%2031.%20But%20even%20that%20did%20not%20happen.%20In%20these%20circumstances%20the%20AITC%20chairperson%20(Banerjee)%20is%20of%20the%20view%20that%20if%20anybody%20can%20defeat%20the%20BJP%20in%20Bengal%20it%20is%20the%20TMC.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%20was%20the%20very%20idea%20behind%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20added%20referring%20to%20the%20goal%20of%20defeating%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDev%20said%20that%20Banerjee%20is%20clear%20about%20working%20with%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20on%20a%20national%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%