n-of-uavs-employed-by-houthi-forces-in-yemen%2F%5C%22%3Edomestic%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.conflictarm.com%2Fperspectives%2Firanian-technology-transfers-to-yemen%2F%5C%22%3Eweapon%20production%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20airstrikes%20alone%20are%20unlikely%20to%20deliver%20a%20knockout%20blow%20to%20their%20military%20capacity%20and%20will%20almost%20certainly%20increase%20their%20appetite%20for%20a%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20because%20they%20can%20%E2%80%93%20for%20the%20first%20time%20%E2%80%93%20more%20strongly%20frame%20their%20actions%20in%20the%20context%20of%20fighting%20against%20the%20US%20and%20Israel%2C%20per%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwaleedmahdi.com%2Fechoes-of-a-scream%2F%5C%22%3Eslogan%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CGod%20is%20Great%2C%20death%20to%20America%2C%20death%20to%20Israel%2C%20a%20curse%20upon%20the%20Jews%2C%20victory%20to%20Islam.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWith%20dissent%20rising%2C%20the%20Houthis%20have%20found%20%E2%80%98quasi-legitimacy%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20reason%20they%20are%20unlikely%20to%20be%20deterred%20is%20more%20important%2C%20but%20less%20understood%2C%20because%20it%20is%20about%20Yemen%E2%80%99s%20domestic%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Houthis%20currently%20control%20much%20of%20Yemen%2C%20including%20the%20capital%20Sana%E2%80%99a%2C%20which%20accounts%20for%20around%2070%25%20of%20the%20population.%20The%20people%20in%20these%20regions%20have%20been%20subjected%20to%20years%20of%20acute%20and%20structural%20violence%20by%20the%20Houthis.%20This%20includes%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3Ethe%20forced%20disappearances%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2015%2F09%2F15%2Fyemen-houthis-disappear-political-opponent%5C%22%3Epolitical%20opponents%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2023%2F05%2F30%2Fyemen-houthis-forcibly-disappear